<h3>Limitador de data</h3>
<p>Com o limitador de data, você pode definir a data minima entre dois inputs relacionados. Para esssa funcionalidade é necessário inserir as classes <code>.date-range</code> englobando os <code>inputs</code> junto com as classes <code>.to-date</code> ou <code>.from-date</code> de acordo com os exemplos abaixo.</p>
<div class="example">
  <form>
    <div class="row date-range">
      <div class="col-lg-3">
        <label for="example1" class="sr-only">Data</label>
        <div class="input-group datepicker">
          <input type="text" class="form-control date-mask from-date" placeholder="dd/mm/aaaa">
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-3">
        <label for="example1" class="sr-only">Data</label>
        <div class="input-group datepicker">
          <input type="text" class="form-control date-mask to-date" placeholder="dd/mm/aaaa">
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </form>
</div>
<pre class="lang-html linenums prettyprint-code">
<form>
  <div class="row date-range">
    <div class="col-lg-3">
      <label for="example1" class="sr-only">Data</label>
      <div class="input-group datepicker">
        <input type="text" class="form-control date-mask from-date" placeholder="dd/mm/aaaa">
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-lg-3">
      <label for="example1" class="sr-only">Data</label>
      <div class="input-group datepicker">
        <input type="text" class="form-control date-mask to-date" placeholder="dd/mm/aaaa">
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</form>
</pre>

<h3>Data Minima</h3>
<p>Utilize o atributo <code>data-min-date=""</code> para definir uma data minima.</p>
<div class="example">
  <form>
    <div class="row date-range">
      <div class="col-lg-3">
        <label for="example1" class="sr-only">Data</label>
        <div class="input-group datepicker">
          <input type="text" data-min-date="today" class="form-control date-mask to-date" placeholder="dd/mm/aaaa">
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </form>
</div>
